commit.message: Merge dropping of 3.3 support, which should fix Travis. Close #147. Fix #146.
Remove Python 3.3 from the trove classifiers.
Remove py3.3 in travis-ci
Add ascii flag
Bump version to 0.8.1, and update readme.
use print function for Python 3 compatibility
Bump version to 0.8.0, and bring version history up to date.
Update trove classifiers to match tox build matrix.

Improve text representation and thus error messages for anonymous nodes. Close #113.

Nodes now reference their creating expressions directly as a result.
Remove superfluous list construction.
Add six to tox dependencies for speed.
Move equality logic into base class.
Remove cruft from docstring.
Add docstrings to document test intent.
Delimit error message per https://github.com/erikrose/parsimonious/pull/113/files#r118736898
Factor identity and hash checks into a single place where possible.
Fix failing repr test in python 2.
Add tests for improved visitor display.
Show the full rule definition rather than just the (possibly blank) name.
Fix test failures resulting from altering the structure of Node.
Have Node store a reference to the expression that created it.
Clarify some NodeVisitor docs.

Put quotes around (sometimes-empty) rule name in missing-visitor error message.

This was confusing people, as in #110.

I also did an audit of the rest of the %s occurrences in the codebase, and no other obviously beneficial quotes are missing.

Make Grammar iteration ordered. Close #108.

This makes life easier for visualizers like #104 and might make our `__repr__`s more like the original input as well.
Add test reproducing StrAndRepr.__repr__ issue.
